We are a venture-backed SaaS cybersecurity company (stealth) solving the largest and most complex problem in cybersecurity: social engineering.

Social engineering is not about technology infrastructure. It is about people sharing information with other people, and a vast body of valuable information at the fingertips of attackers who know how to make use of it.

That is why this is the largest cyber problem facing society today. Role Description: Vice President of Engineering (member of leadership team)

As a key member of the leadership team, the VP of Engineering is responsible for the technical delivery of our solution to sophisticated enterprise cybersecurity customers.

In this role, you will be responsible for: --Managing the engineering organization from front-end UI to the collection and analysis of unstructured data;

+Aligning the technical roadmap against the product roadmap and business needs to deliver capability-rich SaaS solutions on time;

+Establishing, monitoring, and communicating KPIs to the rest of the executive team and Board of Directors; Improving engineering efficiency over time -- both in terms of technical efficiency and team dynamics;

+Increasing the technical value of the company over time through strong management and by crossing new technical ground;

Qualifications We believe successful candidates will likely have some or all of following:

+Demonstrated success leading distributed teams of software engineers and data scientists who build cutting edge SaaS solutions as a VP of Engineering or similar role (CTO, Senior Director, or Director of Engineering);

+Both the social and technical ability to grow an existing engineering organization through coaching, hiring, and recruiting to support the proper team growth and technical architecture;

+Managerial and organizational skills for a coordinated large team over time;

EPSY HEALTH | Multiple Roles (f/m/x) | Remote | HQs:London, UK and Houston, Texas | Full-Time | https://www.epsyhealth.com

Epsy is on a mission to give the world a better way to live with epilepsy. Epsy is the leading digital health platform empowering patients, caregivers and healthcare providers in their journey for the treatment of epilepsy. We won the 2020 Google Material Design Award, two 2021 CES Innovation Awards, and were honoured for 2021 Best Apps by the Webby Awards.

We are a startup, but operate under the umbrella of a multi-billion dollar corporate.

We're looking for Software Engineers and Leaders across a variety of roles, including:

- Senior Back-End engineer;

- Senior Android engineer;

- Senior Web front-end engineer;

- Senior Product Designer;

- Marketing Manager;

Enquiries and applications for all roles: hiring <at> epsyhealth.com or https://www.epsyhealth.com/work-with-us
